HEADWORD: Glama
<hw>Gla"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.; cf. Gr. <?/,
L. <ets>gramiae</ets>, Gr. <?/ blear-eyed.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A copious gummy secretion of the humor of the eyelids, in
consequence of some disorder; blearedness; lippitude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

